Starbucks Corporation receives and processes the personal information of customers of its wholly-owned subsidiaries in the European Union and Switzerland. While the extent of personal information collected varies from country to country, below is a description of how personal information that is transferred to the United States is collected, processed, shared, and protected.
Starbucks collects the personal information customers give to us such as first or last name, username, password, email address, postal address, phone number, financial account information such as credit card number, birthday, city of birth and demographic information and any other information they choose to give us.  They may also permit us to access information stored in the “contacts list” on their device or provide us with information regarding the person they direct us to send a gift certificate or e-gift online. 
Starbucks also collects information when customers access or use our websites or mobile applications, including placing orders, or visit our stores, such as purchasing information (for example products purchased, purchase location, frequency of purchases, rewards or promotions associated with purchases, and products on “wish list” for future purchase), device and usage information (for example, type of device, operating system, browser, internet service provider, domain name, IP address, UDID,  the website that referred a user, web pages viewed including date and time of requests, services or functionality accessed or used (including data and time of access or use), and subject of ads clicked or scrolled), location information, and in-store camera information.  Starbucks also collects information our customers post on other publicly available services, for example information submitted to a blog or social network.  We may also collect information about customers from other companies and organisations.
Starbucks uses the information collected in a variety of ways, including:
•         to process purchases of products and services;
•         to facilitate the functionality of our websites and mobile applications;
•         to deliver gift certificates or e-gifts in accordance with your instructions;
•         to communicate about orders, purchases, returns, accounts, programs;
•         to respond to customer service enquiries and requests for information;
•         to post a customer’s comments or statements on our websites;
•         to send personalized promotions and special offers;
•         to inform customers about our products, services, contests, sweepstakes events, or other promotions;
•         to maintain and improve our websites, mobile applications and the products and services we offer;
•         to detect, prevent, or investigate security breaches or fraud; 
•         to maintain accurate and appropriate records for internal administrative purposes; and 
•         to evaluate and communicate about franchise opportunities
Starbucks may also share information collected about customers with the following parties in the following circumstances:
•         With Starbucks subsidiaries, and affiliated companies for proper management, analysis and decision making, including decisions regarding franchises, the expansion and promotion of our product and service offerings, order or customer request fulfillment, operation of our websites and mobile applications. 
•         With service providers that provide us with support services, such as credit card processing, website hosting, email delivery,  location mapping, postal mail processing, order fulfilment and delivery, and analytics, subject to contractual terms prohibiting such service providers from using or disclosing such information except as necessary to provide their services or as required by law.
•         With business entities or people involved in a merger or other situation involving the transfer of some of all of our business assets subject to a contractual requirement of confidentiality. 
•         With law enforcement and other governmental entities if disclosure is required by law or is necessary to enforce our agreements or policies. . 
•         With other companies or entities with the consent of the customer that is the subject of such information.
Starbucks protects personal information the personal information of customers of wholly-owned subsidiaries in the European Union and Switzerland using technical, physical and administrative security measures to reduce the risk of loss, misuse, unauthorized access, disclosure or modification of personal information. Starbucks deploys security safeguards such as firewalls, data encryption, physical access controls, and administrative informational controls. Highly sensitive information (such as a credit card number) transmitted through our website or in one of our mobile applications, is encrypted using the Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) protocol.
